<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[198,301,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks</emphasis>
. Described from the 
<typeStatus box="[562,664,229,255]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">holotype</typeStatus>
and allotype from: 
<collectingCountry box="[909,1012,229,255]" name="Pakistan" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, Punjab, Lyallpur [=Faisalabad], at light, 
<date box="[220,310,268,294]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1929-10-10">
<number box="[220,252,268,294]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="10.0">10</number>
.x. 
<number box="[276,310,268,294]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="29.0">29</number>
</date>
, K.A.S. Rahman (ZSI). The above material is identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[1010,1090,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Maiestas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pruthii">
<emphasis box="[1010,1090,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">pruthii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the original figures and those of 
<bibRefCitation author="Dash" box="[260,612,306,332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="20" refString="Dash, P. C. &amp; Viraktamath, C. A. (2001) Deltocephaline leafhopper genus Goniagnathus (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae) in the Indian subcontinent with descriptions of four new species. Journal of the Bombay Natural History Society, 98 (1), 62 - 79." type="journal article" year="2001">
Dash &amp; Viraktamath (
<number box="[535,603,306,332]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, although all have the characteristic reticulate forewing venation, the 
<collectingCountry box="[320,425,345,371]" name="Pakistan" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
material has a slightly more strongly curved aedeagus and shorter apical process compared to Indian material (compare 
<figureCitation box="[607,689,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="35.[151,256,1683,1707]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,205,1642]" captionTargetId="figure@35.[151,1436,194,1659]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 13. Maiestas pruthii (Metcalf), a, b, head and thorax dorsal view; c, d, forewings; e – f, male genital capsule, lateral view and dorsal view; g-j, anal tube, dorsal, ventral, lateral and posterior view respectively; k, subgenital plate; l – m, aedeagus, lateral view and dorsal apex; n, style." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/193671/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Fig. 
<number box="[660,689,384,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
l with Dash &amp; Virtaktamath, 
<number box="[1030,1091,384,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1998.0">1998</number>
, fig. 
<number box="[1150,1198,384,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="154.0">154</number>
).
</paragraph>
