</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,462,720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis box="[198,301,578,603]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks</emphasis>
. A sub-brachypterous form occurs in the female of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1157,1257,578,604]" name="Pakistan" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(Plate 
<number box="[1353,1370,578,604]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2.0">2</number>
c). In addition, a form with a slightly more elongate aedeagus with a slight lateral flange is present (compare 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="34.[151,255,2009,2033]" captionTargetBox="[270,1305,1343,2008]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[219,1328,1343,2014]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 12. Maiestas subviridis (Metcalf). Aedeagus typical (a, b), atypical (cd); a, d dorsal, b, c, lateral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/193670/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Figs 
<number box="[151,181,656,682]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
a-d). The 
<typeStatus box="[301,353,656,682]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
of this species and various other specimens from throughout its range were examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Webb" box="[151,490,694,720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="21" refString="Webb, M. D., and C. A. Viraktamath. (2009). Annotated check-list, generic key and new species of Old World Deltocephalini leafhoppers with nomenclatorial changes in the Deltocephalus group and other Deltocephalinae (Hemiptera, Auchenorrhyncha, Cicadellidae). Zootaxa. 2163, 1 - 64" type="journal article" year="2009">
Webb &amp; Viraktamath (
<number box="[417,482,694,720]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="2009.0">2009</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
